      <div class="msgContentFrame">When you say making Glad into a paladin I assume you mean the mix of abilities and spells that makes them more sustainable in combat both solo and party. Here are some suggestions. Mix-and-match how you want as you level. I'll place an asterisk after abilities that are fairly mainstay. <br /> <br />Cross-class stuff <br />CNJ 4 - *Cure / THM 4 - Sacrifice <br />CNJ 8 - *Shock Spikes (very good for solo when you don't care about skillups <br />CNJ16 - *Protect/Shell (great to have for solo) <br />THM 8 - Slow (good hate generator) <br />THM10 - Punishing Barbs (for large mobs) <br />THM16 - *Stygian Spikes (MP regen) <br />MAR10 - Defender (although this is not really worthwhile in parties) <br />MAR16 - Disorient (stackable enmity ability) <br /> <br />Other Gladiator stuff that is worthwhile situationally: <br />Rampart (multiple target tanking/solo) <br />Obsess (single target tanking) <br />*Provoke / Taunt (obvious, and good for skillups in party too) <br />*Phalanx (best enmity generator) <br />Still Precision (for landing Phalanx) <br /> <br />Second Wind isn't useful outside of solo btw. As for DEX, just know that it only affects critical hits right now, and does not modify accuracy in any way. That said, the enmity a gladiator will generate from melee attacks is insignificant when compared to how it can gain enmity otherwise. When you party, this becomes very obvious. Keep your VIT capped at all times. MND for MP is not all that important, and once you get Stygian Spikes, you'll find you can regain MP back fairly quickly, making the size of your MP pool less important than prior. <br /> <br />This is all the pre-20 stuff from other classes. It is up to you how to use them. I may have also missed a few, but in general this list is fairly complete for the level range. <br /> <br />Hope this helps. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 26th 2010  8:37pm by GreyJorildyn </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 26th 2010  8:39pm by GreyJorildyn </span></i></div>
