      <div class="msgContentFrame">@14 I have my Gla setup as follows: <br />Cure II <br />Radiance <br />Damnation <br />Bloodbath <br />Defender (on/off ability, don't always use it) <br />Rampart (on/off ability, don't always use it) <br />Phalanx <br />Protect (only use it soloing) <br /> <br />I still need to get stigian spikes for solo, but other than that, I avoid most aoe buffs, since they suck MP, and a good healer at my level should have them anyways. <br /> <br />I try and focus on damage for hate, and ability cure (I still have to level pug for taunt, blindside, and second wind) <br />The nice thing is that bloodbath can stack with damnation, radiance or phalanx.  So, if I don't get a chance for phalanx, I switch it to radiance and/or damnation (if I miss), and the HP return is based off damage, so I only use light stab as a last resort. <br /> <br />The combination of MP regain, and HP regain come in handy, and to be honest, I really don't need anything more than Cure II as an emergency solo or in a party (again, if I have a main healer).  And since phalanx requires so little TP, as long as my shield isn't failing me, I can keep up with hate quite well (ok, below 20... I know I will need much more than that after 20, but I should have more ability points to compensate). <br /></div>
